  "description": [
    "Courrier de France7 BOY SCOUT JAMBOREE HELD NEAR PARIS AUGUST 9TH TO 21ST From August 9th to 21st some 3 000 Boy Scouts representing 54 countries encamped at Moisson near Paris for a great Peace Jam boree The United States sent a delegation of over 1100 boys Other delegations present included those of Austria Canada China Egypt Great Britain and its dependen cies France and its Oversea Terri tories the Scandinavian countries the South American countries Czechoslovakia Burma Iran Cy prus and the Philippines The scouts were housed in a city of tents provided with running water and electricity that sprung up as if by magic in a wooded region where formerly the pheasant was king In three short months the French National Railroads created a special station on the ParisVer non lines known as RosnyJam boree In a wooden barracks scouts or former scouts who are professional journalists press pho tographers and cartoonists edited and published a special eightpage daily called JamboreeFrance The American delegation which disembarked at Antwerp on Aug ust 2nd gave a daybyday demon stration of American methods of camping On August 16th they presented a great parade tracing the progress of democracy in Amer ica"
  ],
